               <p>ELIZABETH SMITH. I am the wife of Charles Smith. The prisoner was in my employ; I gave him a 10l. note between twelve and one o'clock on the 4th of April, to get change; my husband is a <rs id="t18290611-199-viclabel1046" type="occupation">bookbinder</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290611-199-victim1519 t18290611-199-viclabel1046"></join>, and I keep a lodging-house - he was employed to clean knives and shoes, and to go on errands; he never came back with the note nor change - I bad sent for it to pay a small debt; I did not owe him any wages.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290611-199-person1520">
                  ELIZABETH 
                  SMITH
               <interp inst="t18290611-199-person1520" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
