                     <interp inst="t18290611-199-person1520" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , JUN. I saw my mother give him the note; he had been two months with us.</p>
               <p>CHARLES SMITH. The prisoner was in my employ; I met him in the City, very gaily dressed, on Easter Tuesday- I hardly knew him; he begged I would not take him before Mrs. Smith, as he was quite ashamed to see her.</p>
